    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.9-11_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">9</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        McCredie, Missouri
                        October 13, 1958
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>English Department</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>University of Missouri</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear Sir:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am one of your unseen television students and am thoroughly enjoying your Songs of Epic America but would like so much to meet you in person. I'm not sure how this can be accomplished as I teach third grade in a rural consolidated school in Callaway County. My free hours are after 3:30 during the school week. I live only about thirty minutes from Columbia City limits but coming across town to Jesse Hall usually means twenty additional minutes.</p>
                
                <p>I understood when I enrolled for this course that the test would probably be given on a Saturday morning but that I would be notified by mail and would also get some study guides for the course. To date I have had no correspondence from the unviersity.</p>
                
                <p>It will be necessary for me to miss two <hi rend="caps">TV</hi> sessions November and 5th and 6th. I am required to go to State Teachers <del>S</del> Convention those two dates in Kansas City.</p>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.9-11_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">10</fw>
                
                <p>I live on a farm with my husband and an eleven year old daughter. Last winter I took an extension course from the University under Dr. Charlotte Wells in <hi rend="underline">Speech Correction</hi>. That was my first earning of college credit in fifteen years. I found it very interesting and find your course even more stimulating. Several of my friends are listening to you after hearing me talk so enthusiastically about your book of songs and your gifted way of reading them.</p>
                
                <p>I'm looking forward to meeting you at mid-term exams at least.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Lola Jones</signed>
                
                    <signed>Mrs. Leroy Jones</signed>
                    <address><addrLine>McCredie, Mo.</addrLine></address>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
